# Entra Local — node-cli (device code) environment reference
#
# NOTE: this sample reads values directly from process.env and does NOT auto-load a .env file.
# Either export these in your shell before `npm start`, or use your own loader. Every value has a
# default (shown below) that matches the emulator's seeded demo directory.
#
# Certificate trust is automatic: by default the CLI reads the emulator's dev certificate from the
# repo-root data/tls/cert.pem and trusts it for the HTTPS calls MSAL and Graph make, so you normally
# don't need to set anything. Override the path only if your cert.pem lives elsewhere.

# Path to the emulator's self-signed dev certificate, trusted for the device-code + Graph HTTPS calls.
# Relative paths resolve against the directory you run `npm start` from (this node-cli/ folder).
#   - Emulator started with `npm start` from the repo root:  (default, no need to set)
#   - Emulator started with this sample's docker compose:     ./.emulator-data/tls/cert.pem
# EMULATOR_CA_CERT=./.emulator-data/tls/cert.pem

# Optional fallback: still honoured if EMULATOR_CA_CERT is unset. NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS is also the
# standard msal-node recipe (it must be set BEFORE Node starts to affect the global trust store; the
# CLI additionally reads the file explicitly so it works either way).
# NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS=../../data/tls/cert.pem

# Optional overrides (defaults shown):
EMULATOR_ORIGIN=https://localhost:8443
TENANT_ID=11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
CLIENT_ID=cccccccc-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
SCOPE=User.Read
